    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5- 10 min to prep, so get your slow cooker and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Turn on your <strong>slow cooker</strong> to high</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-beef-stroganoff-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel your<strong> brown onion[s] </strong>and chop into wedges</p><p>Crush your <strong>garlic</strong> open by squashing with the side of a knife and remove the skin</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-beef-stroganoff-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferable non-stick) over a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced beef </strong>and <strong>onion wedges </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until the beef is browned</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-beef-stroganoff-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the beef is browning, roughly crumble in your <strong>white cup mushrooms</strong>, then add your <strong>tomato</strong> <strong>paste</strong>, <strong>red wine vinegar</strong> and most of your <strong>ground smoked</strong> <strong>paprika</strong> (save a pinch for garnish!) with the <strong>crushed</strong> <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Sprinkle in your<strong> beef stock mix </strong>with 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong>, your <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>Dijon mustard </strong>and 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[425ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-beef-stroganoff-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once boiling, transfer everything from the pan to the <strong>slow cooker</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up, then cover and cook on high for 4 hours \u2013 this is your <strong>beef stroganoff</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-beef-stroganoff-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the beef stroganoff has 15 min left, boil a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>pasta </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the pasta for 7-9 min (10-12 min for wholewheat) or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the pasta</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-beef-stroganoff-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the beef stroganoff is done, stir through your <strong>cooked pasta </strong>and most of your <strong>soured cream</strong> (save some for garnish!) \u2013 this is your<strong> slow cooker beef stroganoff tortiglioni</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-beef-stroganoff-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>To serve, dollop the<strong> reserved soured cream </strong>over the <strong>slow cooker beef stroganoff tortiglioni </strong>and sprinkle over the <strong>remaining ground smoked paprika</strong></p><p>Season with a grind of<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Dig in!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
